race.description: Haneco - Electra - Gts - Klein Tools Mdn Plate
race.comment: Small field with some handy types engaged. SUPER SCOTCH (5) closed late on debut with a respectable third over 1500m at Kembla Grange. Drops in weight now and looks to have the necessary upside to take a hand in the finish. Expect to see him a little closer to the speed. SIR LOYNE (4) bounced off his even debut fifth to Shangri La Boy, with a determined on-pace second over 1600m at Hawkesbury. Set to peak from the low draw and gets every chance. MONTAIGNE (7) bounced out quickly on resumption before folding up late in the straight when fourth over 1400m at Randwick Kensington. Likely to roll forward from the sticky gate and take catching. MADE IN ITALY (8) drifted back again at her second race start before launching late with a slashing third over 1500m at Kembla Grange. Key jockey change for this from the better draw. Value prospect.
